<main>
  <h1>üåº Eighth Month of Pregnancy (Week 29‚Äì32)</h1>
  <p class="subtitle"><strong>This is the final trimester phase where the baby gains fat, brain develops rapidly, and the mother may experience increased discomfort.</strong></p>

  <!-- Baby Growth -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">üë∂ Baby Growth</h2>
    <ul>
      <li class="do-item">Baby size: ~ 40‚Äì45 cm, 1.8‚Äì2.3 kg</li>
      <li class="do-item">Brain development very fast ‚Äî baby can hear, respond to light & sound</li>
      <li class="do-item">Lungs continue maturing (getting ready for breathing)</li>
      <li class="do-item">Baby starts moving to head-down position</li>
      <li class="do-item">Strong kicks ‚Äî less space to move</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Mother's Body Changes -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">ü§∞ Mother's Body Changes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li class="do-item">Shortness of breath due to uterus pushing diaphragm</li>
      <li class="do-item">More frequent urination</li>
      <li class="do-item">Back pain & pelvic pressure</li>
      <li class="do-item">Swelling in legs/feet (normal unless sudden)</li>
      <li class="do-item">White discharge increases (normal unless smelly/itchy)</li>
      <li class="do-item">Difficulty sleeping</li>
      <li class="do-item">False contractions (Braxton Hicks)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Diet -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">üçΩÔ∏è Foods to Eat</h2>
    <ul>
      <li class="do-item">Iron-rich foods: Spinach, beetroot, broccoli, jaggery, dates</li>
      <li class="do-item">Protein: Eggs, milk, curd, paneer, fish/chicken (well cooked), dal</li>
      <li class="do-item">Calcium: Ragi, almonds, sesame seeds, milk products</li>
      <li class="do-item">Hydration: 8‚Äì10 glasses of water</li>
      <li class="do-item">Fiber: Whole grains, fruits, vegetables to prevent constipation</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Foods to Avoid -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">üö´ Foods to Avoid</h2>
    <ul>
      <li class="avoid-item">Street food / unhygienic foods</li>
      <li class="avoid-item">Too much salt ‚Üí swelling ‚Üë</li>
      <li class="avoid-item">Papaya and pineapple (in large quantity)</li>
      <li class="avoid-item">Excessive sugary foods</li>
      <li class="avoid-item">Unpasteurized milk & cheese</li>
      <li class="avoid-item">Undercooked meat/eggs</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Exercises -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">üßò‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Exercises & Activity</h2>
    <ul>
      <li class="do-item">Walking 30 mins/day</li>
      <li class="do-item">Pelvic floor (Kegel) exercises</li>
      <li class="do-item">Light prenatal yoga (doctor recommended)</li>
      <li class="do-item">Sleep on left side ‚Äî improves blood flow</li>
      <li class="avoid-item">Avoid heavy lifting or standing long hours</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Warning Symptoms -->
  <div class="emergency-box">
    <h2 class="section-title">‚ö†Ô∏è Warning Symptoms</h2>
    <ul>
      <li class="avoid-item">Severe abdominal pain or regular contractions</li>
      <li class="avoid-item">Reduced baby movements</li>
      <li class="avoid-item">Heavy bleeding or watery discharge (water break)</li>
      <li class="avoid-item">Severe headache, sudden swelling ‚Üí Pre-eclampsia</li>
      <li class="avoid-item">High fever</li>
      <li class="avoid-item">Vision blurring, dizziness</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Doctor's Tips -->
  <div class="tip-box">
    Drink enough water, stay active daily, maintain calm, and follow doctor's guidance for normal delivery.
  </div>

</main>

